        • [ - ] Castle - member since 08-Sep-15

          @SteveHyland Bournemouth have played brilliantly this season and constantly proved their doubters wrong. I think they're in a upper midtable to stay. However, both their form and schedule have changed recently and rest of the year will be very difficult for them. And their two key players, Fraser and Wilson, have looked quite tired and should be given some rest. It could cost them dearly if they're burned out. Therefore Stanislas, Defoe and Mousset should be given more opportunities. Rotation should be on Pep's mind too as Aguero hasn't looked nearly as sharp as earlier in the season and David Silva and Fernandinho play almost every match. I'd be little surprised if they don't rotate in their home fixture, although Watford aren't at their best right now and are another option to give key players some rest.
